WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.000
Domino's Quick Starter, The Selfish Giant, by Oscar Wilde.

00:07.000 --> 00:09.400
Chapter 1.

00:09.400 --> 00:28.400
The Giant Comes Home Every afternoon, when school finishes,

00:28.400 --> 00:34.000
the children play in the giant's garden.

00:34.000 --> 00:39.680
It's a wonderful, big, green garden.

00:39.680 --> 00:47.720
There are beautiful flowers in it, and twelve tall trees.

00:47.720 --> 00:54.760
Birds like sitting and singing in these trees.

00:54.760 --> 01:00.360
The children often stop playing and listen to them.

01:00.360 --> 01:07.440
We're very happy here, they say.

01:07.440 --> 01:20.600
For seven years, the giant stays away in Cornwall, at the house of his friend, the Cornish giant.

01:21.600 --> 01:30.600
One day, he comes home, and he finds all the children in the garden.

01:30.600 --> 01:36.600
What are you doing here?

01:36.600 --> 01:43.600
He cries angrily, and the children run away.

01:43.600 --> 01:46.600
It's my garden.

01:46.600 --> 01:59.600
The giant says, people must understand, and nobody can play here.

01:59.600 --> 02:02.600
Only me.

02:02.600 --> 02:12.600
So, he puts a wall around the garden, with a big notice on it.

02:12.600 --> 02:16.600
No children.

02:16.600 --> 02:21.600
He is a very selfish giant.

02:21.600 --> 02:26.600
Where can the children go now?

02:26.600 --> 02:37.600
They don't like playing in the road, so, after school, they walk around the wall,

02:37.600 --> 02:47.600
and they look at it, and they remember the beautiful garden behind it too.

02:47.600 --> 03:10.600
Chapter 2 Always Winter

03:10.600 --> 03:28.600
Then, the spring comes.

03:28.600 --> 03:39.600
All over the country, there are spring flowers and little birds in the green trees.

03:39.600 --> 03:45.600
But in the selfish giant's garden, it stays winter.

03:45.600 --> 03:53.600
The birds don't want to sing in it, because there are no children.

03:53.600 --> 03:57.600
The trees there stay dark.

03:57.600 --> 04:05.600
One beautiful flower puts its head up out of the ground,

04:05.600 --> 04:13.600
but it sees the notice and is very sorry for the children.

04:13.600 --> 04:20.600
So, it goes back under the ground and sleeps again.

04:20.600 --> 04:24.600
Nobody is happy about this.

04:24.600 --> 04:29.600
Only the snow and the frost.

04:29.600 --> 04:33.600
Spring doesn't come to this garden.

04:33.600 --> 04:43.600
Then they cry, so we can live here all year.

04:43.600 --> 04:57.600
The snow puts her cold white coat on the ground, and the frost puts silver on the dark trees.

04:57.600 --> 05:00.600
They tell the North wind,

05:00.600 --> 05:04.600
you must stay with us.

05:04.600 --> 05:11.600
So he comes in his big brown coat.

05:11.600 --> 05:23.600
He makes lots of noise up and down the garden, and he moves things here and there all day.

05:23.600 --> 05:27.600
This is wonderful!

05:27.600 --> 05:29.600
He cries.

05:29.600 --> 05:35.600
Let's ask the hail here too.

05:35.600 --> 05:39.600
So, the hail comes.

05:39.600 --> 05:49.600
Every day, he sits on the roof of the giant's big old house.

05:49.600 --> 05:57.600
He never stops hitting it noisily, hour after hour.

05:57.600 --> 06:02.600
His suit is the color of smoke.

06:02.600 --> 06:10.600
And cold smoke comes from his mouth when he opens it.

06:10.600 --> 06:16.600
The selfish giant sits at his window.

06:16.600 --> 06:22.600
He looks out at his cold white garden.

06:22.600 --> 06:25.600
I don't understand.

06:25.600 --> 06:27.600
He says.

06:27.600 --> 06:31.600
The spring's very late this year.

06:31.600 --> 06:34.600
When is it coming?

06:34.600 --> 06:39.600
And when is this winter finishing?

06:46.600 --> 07:01.600
Chapter 3

07:01.600 --> 07:04.600
The Hole in the Wall

07:16.600 --> 07:26.600
The spring and the summer never come to the giant's garden.

07:26.600 --> 07:39.600
The autumn brings golden apples to most people's gardens, but to the giant's garden she brings nothing.

07:39.600 --> 07:43.600
I don't give to selfish people.

07:43.600 --> 07:45.600
She says.

07:45.600 --> 07:50.600
So, it is always winter there.

07:50.600 --> 08:00.600
And the north wind, the hail, the frost and the snow run about in it.

08:00.600 --> 08:07.600
One morning, when the giant opens his eyes in bed,

08:07.600 --> 08:13.600
he hears some music.

08:13.600 --> 08:16.600
That's beautiful.

08:16.600 --> 08:18.600
He cries.

08:18.600 --> 08:20.600
But what is it?

08:20.600 --> 08:25.600
A little bird is singing near his window.

08:25.600 --> 08:27.600
That's all.

08:27.600 --> 08:36.600
But after the long winter in his garden, the giant can't remember the noise very well.

08:36.600 --> 08:42.600
Then, the hail stops hitting the roof.

08:42.600 --> 08:46.600
And the north wind is quiet.

08:46.600 --> 08:57.600
Suddenly, a wonderful perfume comes to the giant through the open window.

08:57.600 --> 09:02.600
The spring's here at last, I think.

09:02.600 --> 09:04.600
He cries.

09:04.600 --> 09:09.600
Then, he gets up and looks out.

09:09.600 --> 09:13.600
What a wonderful thing.

09:13.600 --> 09:22.600
The children are coming into the garden through a little hole in the wall.

09:22.600 --> 09:26.600
And they are sitting in the trees.

09:26.600 --> 09:34.600
And the trees are happy because the children are back.

09:34.600 --> 09:40.600
They begin to blossom and move their arms about.

09:40.600 --> 09:46.600
The birds are singing happily in the sky.

09:46.600 --> 09:53.600
The flowers are coming out of the ground and laughing.

09:54.600 --> 10:03.600
But far across the garden, in one corner, it isn't spring.

10:03.600 --> 10:08.600
A young boy is standing there.

10:08.600 --> 10:13.600
There is frost and snow on his tree.

10:13.600 --> 10:22.600
And he cannot get up into it, so he is crying.

10:22.600 --> 10:43.600
Chapter 4 The Boy in the Tree

10:43.600 --> 10:59.600
Get up, little boy.

10:59.600 --> 11:04.600
Says the tree in that corner of the garden.

11:04.600 --> 11:12.600
And it puts its branches nearer the ground for the young boy.

11:12.600 --> 11:18.600
But he is very little and he can't get on them.

11:18.600 --> 11:29.600
The giant watches from his window and his cold heart is suddenly warmer.

11:29.600 --> 11:32.600
Now I see.

11:32.600 --> 11:34.600
He cries.

11:34.600 --> 11:42.600
The spring doesn't come here because I'm selfish.

11:42.600 --> 11:45.600
He is truly sorry.

11:45.600 --> 11:49.600
I know, he says.

11:49.600 --> 11:59.600
I can put the little boy up in the tree and knock down the wall.

11:59.600 --> 12:07.600
Then the children can always play in my garden.

12:07.600 --> 12:16.600
So he goes quietly down to his front door and he opens it.

12:16.600 --> 12:22.600
Then he goes out into the garden.

12:22.600 --> 12:29.600
When the children see him, they are very afraid.

12:29.600 --> 12:33.600
So they all run away.

12:33.600 --> 12:39.600
And it is winter in the garden again.

12:39.600 --> 12:46.600
But the little boy has his head in his hands.

12:46.600 --> 12:50.600
He can't see the giant.

12:50.600 --> 12:58.600
So the giant goes very quietly over to him.

12:58.600 --> 13:10.600
He takes the little boy carefully in his hand and he puts him up in the tree.

13:10.600 --> 13:21.600
At once the tree blossoms and the birds come and sing in it.

13:21.600 --> 13:32.600
Then the little boy puts his arms around the giant's neck and he kisses him.

13:32.600 --> 13:38.600
When the other children see this, they understand.

13:38.600 --> 13:43.600
The giant isn't bad anymore.

13:43.600 --> 13:51.600
So they run back into the garden and the spring comes with them.

13:51.600 --> 13:56.600
It's your garden now, little children.

13:56.600 --> 13:59.600
The giant says.

13:59.600 --> 14:07.600
Then he takes a big axe and he knocks down the wall.

14:07.600 --> 14:28.600
Chapter 5.

14:28.600 --> 14:46.600
The most beautiful flowers.

14:46.600 --> 14:54.600
At 12 o'clock that day, the people are going to the shops.

14:54.600 --> 14:58.600
They see the giant.

14:58.600 --> 15:06.600
He is playing with the children in the most beautiful garden.

15:06.600 --> 15:11.600
All day long the children play.

15:11.600 --> 15:19.600
In the evening, they come and say goodbye to the giant.

15:19.600 --> 15:23.600
But where's your little friend?

15:23.600 --> 15:25.600
He asks them.

15:25.600 --> 15:35.600
The young boy is the giant's favorite because he remembers the child's kiss.

15:35.600 --> 15:38.600
We don't know.

15:38.600 --> 15:41.600
One of the children answers.

15:41.600 --> 15:45.600
He isn't here now.

15:45.600 --> 15:50.600
Well, he must come again tomorrow.

15:50.600 --> 15:54.600
Please tell him that.

15:54.600 --> 15:56.600
The giant says.

15:56.600 --> 15:59.600
Where does he live?

15:59.600 --> 16:01.600
We're not sure.

16:01.600 --> 16:04.600
A different child says.

16:04.600 --> 16:08.600
We don't know him.

16:08.600 --> 16:15.600
When the giant hears this, he is very sad.

16:15.600 --> 16:26.600
Every afternoon, when school finishes, the children come and play with the giant.

16:26.600 --> 16:36.600
But the giant's favorite, the little boy, never comes back.

16:36.600 --> 16:42.600
The giant is very nice to all the children.

16:42.600 --> 16:49.600
But he wants to see his first little friend again.

16:49.600 --> 16:53.600
He speaks about him a lot.

16:53.600 --> 16:58.600
I'd like to see him again one day.

16:58.600 --> 17:03.600
He often says.

17:03.600 --> 17:11.600
After many years, the giant is old and weak.

17:11.600 --> 17:15.600
He cannot play anymore.

17:15.600 --> 17:21.600
So he sits in a nice big chair.

17:21.600 --> 17:26.600
And he watches the children's games.

17:26.600 --> 17:32.600
He looks at his garden happily too.

17:32.600 --> 17:37.600
I have many beautiful flowers.

17:37.600 --> 17:39.600
He says.

17:39.600 --> 17:47.600
But the children are the most beautiful flowers of all.

17:47.600 --> 18:11.600
Chapter 6 The Wounds of Love

18:11.600 --> 18:37.600
One winter morning, when he is getting up, the giant looks out of his window.

18:37.600 --> 18:42.600
The winter doesn't matter to him now.

18:42.600 --> 18:50.600
The spring is sleeping at that time of the year he knows.

18:50.600 --> 18:57.600
And the flowers are in their beds under the ground.

18:57.600 --> 19:04.600
Suddenly, he sees something wonderful.

19:04.600 --> 19:09.600
Can it be true?

19:09.600 --> 19:12.600
He cries.

19:12.600 --> 19:27.600
Far across the garden, in one corner, there is a tree with beautiful white blossoms all over it.

19:27.600 --> 19:34.600
There are silver apples on its golden branches.

19:34.600 --> 19:43.600
And the little boy, his favourite, is standing under the tree.

19:43.600 --> 19:49.600
He is all in white.

19:49.600 --> 20:00.600
The giant runs down to his front door and out into the garden.

20:00.600 --> 20:06.600
He goes quickly across it to the child.

20:06.600 --> 20:14.600
But when he comes near, his face is suddenly angry.

20:14.600 --> 20:19.600
Where do these wounds come from?

20:19.600 --> 20:21.600
He cries.

20:21.600 --> 20:31.600
Because there, on the boy's hands, are the wounds of two nails.

20:31.600 --> 20:38.600
And the wounds of two nails are on his little feet.

20:38.600 --> 20:44.600
Who is guilty of this?

20:44.600 --> 20:54.600
Tell me, and I can take my big sword and kill him.

20:54.600 --> 21:04.600
No, the child answers, because these are the wounds of love.

21:04.600 --> 21:08.600
Who are you?

21:08.600 --> 21:16.600
The giant says quietly, and he kneels before the child.

21:16.600 --> 21:25.600
Then, the child smiles at the giant and tells him,

21:25.600 --> 21:32.600
You remember me from before, here in your garden.

21:32.600 --> 21:40.600
And today, you are coming away with me to my garden.

21:40.600 --> 21:45.600
Paradise.

21:45.600 --> 21:52.600
When the children run into the garden that afternoon,

21:52.600 --> 21:57.600
they find the giant under the tree.

21:57.600 --> 22:00.600
He is dead now.

22:00.600 --> 22:07.600
And there are beautiful white blossoms all over him.

